Meru assembly speaker and the Njuri Ncheke Council of Elders have called for tolerance and peaceful campaigns. Thisis after PNU&rsquo;s campaign materials were destroyed at the weekend. On Tuesday,speaker Joseph Kaberia (pictured)said, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s a criminal offence to damage campaign materials of opponents. The police and the IEBC should investigateand bring the culprits to book.&rdquo;